The social card of a resident of the Ivanovo region is recognized as an electronic means of payment.
The amendments preserve the public transport passenger allowance.
From September 24, the procedure for organizing the preferential travel of citizens using the social card of a resident of the Ivanovo region changes.
According to the press service of the Russian government for the Ivanovo region, the changes provide for the preservation of the public passenger transportation privilege and bring the scheme of mutual payments on the social card in accordance with the requirements of Federal Law No. 161 of the Federal Law "On the National Payment System".
At the same time, the social card of the inhabitant of the Ivanovo region is recognized as an electronic means of payment.
And the conditions of its use change accordingly.
So, the limit of replenishment is now set not in trips, as before, but in the amount of money, with the preservation of winter and summer periods - in winter not more than 400 rubles, in the summer period - not more than 800 rubles for the current month.
Now, social card holders will need to keep track of their balance on transport receipts, not the number of remaining trips.
The cost of the preferential travel for citizens will be 1/2 of the carrier's fare.
The rest of the fare is paid by the regional budget.
The replenishment schedule remains the same - from the 24th of the previous month to the 23rd of the current month.
The new social card system will have a number of advantages.
It is possible to keep detailed accounts of the expenditure of money on the social card with pinpoint accuracy.
In addition, it is possible to recover accrued but unspent funds.
We should also add that the scheme of mutual settlements with carriers becomes transparent, since now half of the cost of travel is paid by the citizen, and exactly the same amount is reimbursed to the carrier by the budget.
There is no charge for depositing funds on the card.
In turn, Vasily Silkin, Deputy Head of the Department of Road and Transport of Ivanovo Region, reported that in 2014 more than 33 million trips were made in the region using social cards, in 2015 - almost 25 million trips.
The regional budget provides for more than 470 million rubles for providing citizens with a preferential travel with the use of a social card.
As of September 1, the amount of compensation for these purposes amounted to more than 312 million rubles.
