Jeremy Corbyn makes his debut in the Prime Ministers ' Questions session .
After Mr. Corbyn 's election , his debut at the Prime Minister 's Question Session is eagerly awaited .
New Labour leader Jeremy Corbyn will soon be making his first appearance at the Prime Minister's Question Time, taking on David Cameron for the first time.
Mr Corbyn will deliver the first of six scheduled questions in the afternoon, and his speech is likely to be closely watched by the press and by Labour MPs.
He called for "less theatre and more facts" in a weekly demonstration speech.
He also stated that he might miss some of the meetings, leaving them to his colleagues.
The meeting will be Mr Corbyn's first parliamentary test as leader; it will follow his appointment of a shadow cabinet and his speech at the annual Trade Union Congress on Tuesday.
Meanwhile, the Labour leader's decision to stand silent during the playing of the national anthem at the service on Tuesday, during the celebration of the 75th anniversary of the Battle of Britain, has drawn criticism from a number of conservative members of Parliament and been the subject of several leading newspaper articles.
