Mr. Maimarakis, welcome to the Euronews!
Vangelis Meimarakis: Thank you for inviting me to your party.
Euronews: Nine months ago, your party suffered a crushing defeat, losing to the Syriza coalition, but now, according to polls, New Democracy is on a par with it in popularity.
What has changed over time?
Vangelis Meimarakis: Greece has changed, and so have we.
Mr. Tsipras lied a lot in January of last year.
Nine months ago, Greece had a budget surplus and prospects for economic growth.
Now the country is back to a deficit and high unemployment.
The investors left because Mr. Tsipras kicked them out.
In the last nine months, the Greeks have had the opportunity to assess the situation the country was in in January and the false promises of Mr. Tsipras.
