The humiliation of the trances by the fellow prisoners is guaranteed, - says Vladislav Grib.
Depending on how big the city is, how many gender-diverse offenders there are, you have to calculate where to put them.
There's no need for a separate cell. Just cells, cells in prisons.
Yes, a separate colony is possible if there are many transgender people.
As Grib explained, the unit can hold 50 or 100 people, and if a specialized unit is created in Russia alone, prisoners from any region can be admitted to serve their sentences.
Citizens are held in the detention center at the place of the crime, so the arrival of transvestites or transgender people from other subjects during the investigation and trial is unrealistic, but to introduce such a practice for those already convicted in a separate colony - yes, "Grib believes.
Recall that the day before, law enforcement officers could not decide in which detention center - male or female - to identify the 24-year-old transsexual Dmitry Kozhukov (known as Alina Davis), who was detained for drug possession, which is why the man with a girl's appearance was not arrested.
He was released on a non-disclosure.
This news was widely discussed on social networks and in the media, as the mechanism of detention of transgender people in SIZO and colonies in Russia is not yet really there.
Russian human rights defender and activist of the LGBT movement (LGBT - lesbians, gays, bisexuals, transsexuals) Nikolai Alekseev supported the idea of creating special places for transgender people to serve their sentences, noting that it is also possible to define people in colonies - male or female - depending on their own desires.
Given the atmosphere in Russian prisons, the sentence is correct.
Yes, it's a very small percentage, but the problem exists, as does the issue of providing security in prisons for homosexuals", Alexeev says.
Prisons should be safe, so separate blocks could be made in the name of that and for homosexuals, especially since there are more of them in prisons than transgender people.
