At the same time, international expert on reproductive health in the Russian Federation, Boris Lordkapianidze, noted that the introduction of a new system for the distribution of transsexuals in the colony could greatly delay the start of the sentence for convicted criminals.
A commission is formed, it's a question of sexology, psychiatrists conduct long-term observations, it's not one test on which to base a highly accurate conclusion.
The facilities of psychiatry today allow it.
That's why potential patients are always examined before they change their gender - they show whether sex change with surgery is a necessary measure, says Lordipanidze.
But I'm having a hard time seeing how this system can be implemented in relation to the prisoners, because the average time it takes to do this is a month.
The doctor, despite generally supporting the idea of creating separate blocks for transsexuals, also doubts that in the current economic conditions it would be advisable to allocate funds for the construction of new premises, medical examinations, - transgender people in Russia units.
It is difficult to calculate, there are no official statistics, but if we consider that homosexuals in Russia are about 5%, then we can say that transgender people are even fewer, and those who have such a deviation and also commit crimes are quite insignificant, - said Lordicpanidze.
Now, by petitioning the colony administration, gays, transgender people can get separate conditions.
